	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>NewRisingSun</b> [ Sun Dec 24, 2017 2:03 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: switching Nestopia to PAL</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Use Nestopia's header editor and choose the INES 2.0 format, which will allow you to select the &quot;PAL&quot; television system in that game's header. Note that Nestopia's internal database will override any iNES header settings, so if you find Nestopia still ignoring the TV System setting, disable Nestopia's internal database in Options-&gt;Database. Note that you will need to reenable the internal database for games using Konami VRC2/VRC4 (Mappers 21,22,23,25) and Mapper 185, as the proper submappers were allocated long after Nestopia development was discontinued, and Nestopia will not load these games at all without an internal database.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
